- "ships sailing the digital seas" refers to servers in operation;
- "for at least a day" means the uptime is 24 hours or more;
- "signals from the shore" symbolizes response times to incoming requests.

sql:
SELECT error_message 
FROM error_logs 
WHERE error_id = 1;

SELECT url, response_time 
FROM performance_metrics 
WHERE response_time > (SELECT AVG(response_time) FROM performance_metrics);
